Prune_taxa gets rid of unwanted indices

**Q**: is the third line of code pruning anything in the ps.top20 object that is not found in top20? So its getting rid of all the other ASVs besides 1-20? 
**Q:**: what are all of the bars/sections within each location? It is many more than 20 OTUS. 

```{r}
top20 <- names(sort(taxa_sums(ps), decreasing=TRUE))[1:20]
